news.title: London unveils public-private partnership to attract real estate investments
news.para: Backed by the UK government and the Mayor of London, the new PPP is aimed at driving business development and cross-border introductions across low-carbon real estate, regeneration, infrastructure, and energy.

news.title: Delhi LG directs DSIIDC to grant six month extension to allottees under relocation scheme
news.para: LG has directed DSIIDC to grant an extension of six months to the allottees in industrial areas of Narela, Bhorgarh and Bawana in the North West Delhi under the relocation scheme for depositing the balance cost of plot and for applying for NOC for construction of factory building," a statement from LG office said.

news.title: Secunderabad: SCB withdraws order on levying fee on residents for extracting groundwater
news.para: SCB has received as many as 55 objections from different stakeholders. “Residents of the Secunderabad Cantonment are being exempted from installation of flow water meters,” SCB chief executive officer (CEO) D Madhukar Naik said after the meeting.

news.title: Maharashtra government invites suggestions and objections for Third Mumbai proposal
news.para: The Third Mumbai largely consists of the area that falls under the recently opened Mumbai Trans Harbour Link (MTHL) influence zone.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government gives freehand to authorities over land usage conversion
news.para: All this while change of land use was carried out with the approval of the government and concerned authority had to put up the file and wait for several months.

news.title: Greater Noida development body reclaims illegally occupied land worth Rs 120 crore
news.para: The demolition drive against the illegal construction was carried out by the local work circle team today. The team has freed about 40,000 square metres of land in Kheda Chauganpur and taken possession of 20,000 square metre land in Bisarkh, freeing it from encroachment," GNIDA's Officer on Special Duty (OSD) Himanshu Verma said.

news.title: Virat Kohli leases 18,340 square feet office space in Gurugram
news.para: According to a person familiar with the deal, Kohli had bought the space about a decade ago and since building recently got completed, he leased the building for rental income.

news.title: House building activity in UK declines at slower rate in February: Survey
news.para: The S&P Global/CIPS Construction Purchasing Mangers' Index (PMI) recovered to 49.7, its highest level since August and up from January's 48.8, but marking a sixth month below the 50 threshold for growth.

news.title: Home sales in Toronto drops by 12% in February 2023
news.para: Home sales in Canada have started to revive in recent months in anticipation of interest rate cuts by the central bank.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government likely to scrap land acquisition in Amaravati
news.para: The state govt plans to withdraw the land acquisition notification for 4,300 acres in Amaravati area, issued in 2016, due to litigations. CRDA and Guntur district administrations are working to complete the withdrawal process before the election notification, sparking controversy with capital city area farmers.

news.title: Unlock lucrative investment opportunities with 'Pehle Dukan Phir Makan Yojana' by the Delhi Mall Complex
Uttar Pradesh government approves construction of Lucknow metro’s second corridor
news.para: Uttar Pradesh govt approved the Charbagh-Vasant Kunj second metro corridor project, which aims to promote green public transport. It will have 12 stations and is expected to be completed within 40 months using tunnel boring machines.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government approves proposal for formation of state capital region
news.para: The primary aim is to foster planned development akin to the Delhi National Capital Region (NCR), an official release issued here said.

news.title: Homebuyers' body FPCE raises RERA functioning issues with housing ministry
news.para: The suggestion from the Forum for People’s Collective Efforts (FPCE) came at a meeting called by the ministry of housing and urban affairs last week.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad property taxpayers encounter technical glitches
news.para: Lingaraj Dharwad Shettar, a social activist and taxpayer, said that some of his friends are trying to pay taxes online but they have remained unsuccessful.

news.title: Patna civic body starts sealing property of 784 tax defaulters
news.para: “To enhance the property tax collection, the teams will visit the households and commercial buildings on Sundays, as well as on the off days for the working class, and the team would facilitate the residents submitting their dues.

news.title: Chandigarh administration says 'won't go ahead' with 2008 housing scheme
news.para: The UT has also decided to refund the money deposited by the petitioners and the other applicants, as per an affidavit submitted by the UT with the HC.

news.title: Haryana cabinet approves land ownership policy for four villages in Hisar
news.para: The residents who have raised construction on an area of up to 250 square yards of land will be granted ownership rights after paying a fee of Rs 2000 per square yard.

news.title: We will continue to grow in Bengaluru & three other cities: Aravind Maiya, Embassy REIT
news.para: Embassy REIT anticipates strong growth in commercial real estate in India, with a focus on cities like Bangalore and plans to enter Chennai. They expect NOI to exceed Rs 3,000 crore in FY24 and have seen positive demand from global capitals for office space.  Plus, they are constructing close to 7 million square feet in our existing parks where the land is already paid for.
